[[Image:CasingCutter002.jpg|thumb|right|upright=1|DSI Casing Cutter details]]
A '''Casing-Cutter''' is a device used in petroleum industry to cut a complete section of a casing, a liner or all others tubular components in a [[well bore]]. This cutting tool is composed by several cutting blades (reinforced with [[Tungsten carbide]]) pivotally mounted on support body. During cutting operations, the cutting blades are gradually deployed outside the support body by hydraulic pressure or mechanical action {{clear}}
